    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46), a quintessential driver\u2019s car featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six power plant. This naturally aspirated mill utilizes individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing to produce a linear power band peaking at 333 hp. Power is delivered to the rear wheels through a crisp Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a torque-sensing limited-slip differential. This example has undergone critical preventative maintenance, including rear subframe reinforcement and a cooling system overhaul with a high-efficiency aluminum radiator. The chassis dynamics are sharpened by a MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension setup, currently fitted with Koni adjustable dampers. While the exterior shows minor patina consistent with a well-enjoyed enthusiast vehicle, the mechanical vitals are robust, with consistent compression across all cylinders and a recent valve adjustment. A purist-spec machine optimized for tactile feedback and longitudinal performance.",
